title: WNBA finals Game 3: A’ja Wilson’s last-gasp winner lifts Aces to brink of title
summary: A’ja Wilson scored a game-winning fadeaway jumper with just 0.3 seconds remaining, leading the Las Vegas Aces to a 90-88 victory over the Phoenix Mercury. This win gives the Aces a commanding 3-0 lead in the WNBA Finals. The dramatic finish highlighted Wilson's clutch performance in a tightly contested matchup.

title: NSW transport bureaucrat admits being given envelopes of cash at Oporto to artificially inflate invoices
summary: Ibrahim Helmy testified at an ICAC hearing that he generated fake invoices as part of an alleged multimillion-dollar kickback scheme. His statements reveal his involvement in fraudulent activities linked to corruption. The case investigates broader allegations of financial misconduct.

title: Chris Minns’ chief of staff in constitutional showdown with parliament over 120-year-old law
summary: James Cullen, called to testify at the Rosehill inquiry, claims that the 1901 law allowing parliament to compel witnesses is unconstitutional. His assertion raises questions about the legality of the inquiry's proceedings. The case could have significant implications for parliamentary oversight and witness testimonies.
